questions.question:
In the figure below, circle O has a radius of 6.  Chord AC is drawn.  What is the length of arc ABC?

[asy]
draw(Circle((0,0),10));
draw((-8,0)--(8,0));
draw((0,-10)--(0,10));
draw((0,0)--dir(150)--dir(210)--cycle);
label("O", (0,0), NE);
label("A", dir(150), NW);
label("B", dir(210), SW);
label("C", (8,0), E);
[/asy]

Statement (1): Angle AOC measures 120 degrees.
Statement (2): The area of triangle AOC is $18\sqrt{3}$.
